---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import ProjectRoadmapStatus from '../../components/ProjectRoadmapStatus.astro';
import { projects } from '../../data/projects';

const project = projects.find((item) => item.subdomain === 'valter');

if (!project) {
  throw new Error('Valter project data not found');
}
---

<DocsLayout title="Valter" description="Central jurisprudence and reasoning backend for the sens.legal ecosystem.">
  <h1>Valter</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Central jurisprudence and reasoning backend</p>

  <span class="badge badge-dev">dev</span>

  <p>
    Valter is the central legal backend of the sens.legal ecosystem. It concentrates
    jurisprudence search, verification, and reasoning over STJ case law, exposing
    those capabilities through REST API and MCP to Juca, other clients, and LLM agents.
  </p>

  <p>
    The current architectural paradigm is <strong>graph-led retrieval</strong>:
    the legal graph in Neo4j becomes the primary discovery path, while lexical
    and semantic search run in parallel as complement and fallback. At the same
    time, backend capabilities that used to live inside Juca are being migrated
    into Valter, consolidating search, reasoning, verification, and future chat
    orchestration in one canonical service.
  </p>

  <h2>Role in the ecosystem</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Canonical backend for jurisprudence and reasoning across the ecosystem</li>
    <li>Main integration surface via REST API and MCP</li>
    <li>Graph-led retrieval with parallel search for support and graceful degradation</li>
    <li>Anti-hallucination verification and traceable reasoning chains</li>
    <li>Destination of the backend migration out of Juca</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Stack</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Language:</strong> Python</li>
    <li><strong>Framework:</strong> FastAPI</li>
    <li><strong>Databases:</strong> PostgreSQL 16, Qdrant, Neo4j / Aura, Redis 7</li>
    <li><strong>Embeddings:</strong> Legal-BERTimbau (768-dim)</li>
    <li><strong>LLM:</strong> Groq API (classification, query expansion)</li>
    <li><strong>Storage:</strong> Cloudflare R2</li>
    <li><strong>Deploy:</strong> Railway</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Roadmap status</h2>

  <ProjectRoadmapStatus project={project} />

  <h2>Links</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://valter.sens.legal" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Documentation</a></li>
    <li><a href="/api/rest">Canonical REST API gateway</a></li>
    <li><a href="/api/mcp">Canonical MCP gateway</a></li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>

